healpix
------------------------------------------
HEALPix is an acronym for Hierarchical Equal Area isoLatitude Pixelization of a
sphere. As suggested in the name, this pixelization produces a subdivision of a
spherical surface in which each pixel covers the same surface area as every
other pixel. The figure below shows the partitioning of a sphere at
progressively higher resolutions, from left to right. The green sphere
represents the lowest resolution possible with the HEALPix base partitioning of
the sphere surface into 12 equal sized pixels. The yellow sphere has a HEALPix
grid of 48 pixels, the red sphere has 192 pixels, and the blue sphere has a
grid of 768 pixels (~7.3 degree resolution).

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.0.7-1
  libcfitsio7-3.470-1
  libchealpix-devel-3.50-1bl1
  libchealpix0-3.50-1bl1
  libgcc1-7.4.0-1
  libgomp1-7.4.0-1
  libhealpix_cxx-devel-3.50-1bl1
  libhealpix_cxx2-3.50-1bl1
  libstdc++6-7.4.0-1
  pkg-config-1.6.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-11-1
  binutils-2.29-1
  bison-3.0.4-1
  cmake-3.14.5-1
  cygport-0.33.1-1
  flex-2.6.4-2
  gcc-core-7.4.0-1
  gcc-fortran-7.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-7.4.0-1
  libtool-2.4.6-7
  make-4.2.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://healpix.jpl.nasa.gov/

Canonical download:
  mirror://sourceforge/healpix/Healpix_3.50_2018Dec10.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack healpix-3.50-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./healpix-3.50-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/healpix-3.50-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/healpix-3.50-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libchealpix0-3.50-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libchealpix-devel-3.50-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libhealpix_cxx2-3.50-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libhealpix_cxx-devel-3.50-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

